        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 6:31PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 630 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Scotland Neck, or 15 miles northeast of Tarboro, moving northeast at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Lewiston Woodville around 650 PM EDT.
Roxobel around 700 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Eagletown, Republican,
Kelford, Burden, and Connaritsa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
